 statistics and a bit of calculus. If you know all those things, then I think a great starting point is the famous [Andrew Ng's course on Machine Learning](https://pt.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning).\n\nYou asked for books and I think you'll find lots of good books on machine learning, but I don't know many of them, I've only read two of'em and one is in Portuguese so I don't think you'll read it, the other one is [Data Mining: Practical Machine Learning Tools and Techniques](https://www.amazon.com/Data-Mining-Practical-Techniques-Management/dp/0123748569), this is also a good starting point and is somewhat easy on the mathematical part of ML, but as I said it's a great starting point and after you've read it you'll know sufficient ML to trace a more specific path of what you want to learn.\n\n&#x200B;", "id": "e4s2cr6", "replies": [{"body": "Can you post the name of the Portuguese one?", "id": "e4s5f4d", "replies": [{"body": "[Intelig\u00eancia Artificial: Uma Abordagem de Aprendizado de M\u00e1quina](https://www.amazon.com.br/Intelig%C3%AAncia-Artificial-Abordagem-Aprendizado-M%C3%A1quina/dp/8521618808)", "id": "e4s64mn", "replies": []}]}, {"body": ">You need to know linear algebra, statistics and a bit of calculus.\n\nok, that's fine, I've had quite a bit of linear algebra and calculus in Uni, I think I should be able to teach myself the things i don't already know :)\n\n\n> starting point and after you've read it you'll know sufficient ML to trace a more specific path of what you want to learn.\n\nthat sounds perfect actually, I think I'm gonna start with this one and the course on machine learning, thank you very much :)", "id": "e4sv4hz", "replies": []}]}], "title": "Resources for learning machine learning"}